A4.text: The Mitsubishi A6M 'Zero' is a long-range carrier-capable fighter aircraft that was manufactured by Mitsubishi Aircraft Company, which was part of Mitsubishi Heavy Industries.

A5.text: It was operated by the Imperial Japanese Navy (IJN) from 1940 to 1945.

A6.text: Mitsubishi Heavy Industries, Ltd. (MHI) is a Japanese multinational engineering, electrical equipment and electronics corporation headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.

A7.text: MHI's automobile division is the predecessor of Mitsubishi Motors.
